{"key":"processedPost-13004405","value":{"id":13004405,"first":13003441,"last":13004405,"when":1280981757,"utime":"08/05/10 07:15 AM","content":"Use your filtered well water.&nbsp; My well also smells like sulfur, but the pH is high, around 9.&nbsp; It's also full of minerals, which is probably a good thing because it works great for mycology.&nbsp; I treat the well with bleach twice a year, and use a charcoal filter for drinking and making agar.&nbsp; I use it right out of the hose for substrates and spraying/misting.&nbsp; It works like a charm.<br /><br />If your pH is very high, add some vinegar to bring it down to about 6 to 7.&nbsp; Order a set of pH test strips.<br />RR","title":"Re: Distilled water?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}